text: Mary Holloway (born 1918) is a female athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== Holloway represented England in the 220 yards and long jump at the 1938 British Empire Games in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia. ==Personal life== Holloway was a typist by trade and lived in Bickley Street, Tooting during 1938. ==References== Category:1918 births Category:English female sprinters Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1938 British Empire Games Category:Possibly living people Category:English female long jumpers
